Name: idiopathic progressive polyneuropathy
Definition: A hypertension occurring during pregnancy characterized by large amounts of protein in the urine (proteinuria) and edema

Name: obsolete idiopathic neuropathy
Definition: A hypertension occurring during pregnancy characterized by large amounts of protein in the urine (proteinuria) and edema

Name: polyneuropathy in collagen vascular disease
Definition: A congenital hypoplastic anemia characterized by progressive pancytopenia with bone marrow failure

Name: obsolete joint disorder
Definition: A congenital hypoplastic anemia characterized by progressive pancytopenia with bone marrow failure
Synonym: Unspecified joint disorder of multiple sites

Name: polyradiculoneuropathy
Definition: A giant cell tumor and bone cancer and bone tissue neoplasm that results_in the presence of multinucleated giant cells (osteoclast-like cell).

Name: demyelinating polyneuropathy
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that involves deficient or defective glycosylation of a variety of tissue proteins and/or lipids.

Name: obsolete ephemeral fever
Definition: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection in cattle

Name: chronic polyneuropathy
Definition: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection in cattle
